# Rocket.new — Debugging Protocol

> Run this protocol on ANY broken Rocket project before writing a single line of fix code.
> Diagnosis first. Fix second. Always.

---

## STEP 1 — RUN THESE IMMEDIATELY ON ANY BROKEN PROJECT

```bash
# 1. TypeScript errors — catches 60% of build failures
npx tsc --noEmit

# 2. Find getSession() in server code — silent auth bug
grep -rn "getSession()" ./app ./lib ./middleware.ts

# 3. Find deprecated Supabase packages
grep -rn "auth-helpers-nextjs" ./app ./lib ./package.json

# 4. Check env vars load
node -e "require('dotenv').config({path:'.env'}); console.log('SUPABASE:', !!process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, 'STRIPE:', !!process.env.STRIPE_SECRET_KEY)"

# 5. Clear Next.js cache (fixes ~20% of weird unexplained issues)
rm -rf .next && npm run dev
```

