## AUTH DEBUGGING DECISION TREE

```
User cannot log in / session not persisting
│
├─ Is middleware.ts at project ROOT (not inside /app)?
│   └─ NO → Move it to root. This is the #1 auth setup mistake.
│
├─ Does middleware.ts call updateSession()?
│   └─ NO → Add: import { updateSession } from '@/lib/supabase/middleware'
│             export async function middleware(request) { return updateSession(request) }
│
├─ Is getUser() used (not getSession()) in server code?
│   └─ grep -rn "getSession()" ./app ./lib
│   └─ FOUND → Replace every instance with getUser() in server-side files
│
├─ Email/password: Does Supabase project have email confirmations on?
│   └─ Supabase Dashboard → Auth → Providers → Email → "Confirm email" toggle
│   └─ If ON: user must confirm before login works
│   └─ Fix: temporarily disable during dev, OR handle "email not confirmed" error
│
├─ Social OAuth (Google/GitHub) not working?
│   ├─ CRITICAL: Social auth ONLY works on live preview URL or custom domain
│   │   It will NEVER work on localhost — this is a Supabase OAuth requirement
│   │   Test on the Netlify deployed URL, not http://localhost:3000
│   │
│   ├─ Is /auth/callback/route.ts present?
│   │   └─ Must call: supabase.auth.exchangeCodeForSession(code)
│   │
│   ├─ Is the Supabase callback URL in Google/GitHub OAuth app settings?
│   │   └─ Must be: https://[project-id].supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
│   │   └─ NOT your app's URL — Supabase handles the OAuth handshake
│   │
│   └─ Are all app URLs in Supabase Auth → URL Configuration?
│       └─ Add: http://localhost:3000, https://[app].netlify.app, https://[custom-domain]
│
└─ Auth works in dev, broken in production?
    └─ Supabase redirect URLs missing production domain → add to URL Configuration
    └─ Env vars missing in Netlify → add all NEXT_PUBLIC_ vars to Netlify dashboard
```

