## STRIPE DEBUGGING DECISION TREE

```
Stripe payment broken
│
├─ Webhook not receiving events?
│   ├─ Is endpoint URL production URL? (Stripe CANNOT reach localhost)
│   │   └─ For local testing: stripe listen --forward-to localhost:3000/api/webhooks/stripe
│   │
│   ├─ Is raw body used? (most common webhook failure)
│   │   └─ grep -n "request.json()" app/api/webhooks/stripe/route.ts
│   │   └─ FOUND → replace with: const body = await request.text()
│   │
│   └─ Does STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET match the endpoint in Stripe dashboard?
│       └─ Each endpoint has a UNIQUE secret — test and live are DIFFERENT
│       └─ Check: Stripe Dashboard → Developers → Webhooks → [endpoint] → Signing secret
│
├─ "No such product/price" error?
│   └─ Using test mode price ID with live keys (or vice versa)
│   └─ Test and live environments are COMPLETELY ISOLATED
│   └─ Fix: recreate products/prices in live mode, update STRIPE_PRICE_ID env var
│
├─ "No such customer" error?
│   └─ Test mode customer IDs (cus_test_xxx) don't exist in live mode
│   └─ Match your env keys with your data environment
│
├─ Payment succeeds but app not updated?
│   └─ Webhook not processing → check Stripe Dashboard → Webhooks → Recent deliveries
│   └─ Look for failed deliveries and click to see the error
│
└─ Stripe form not loading (blank iframe)?
    └─ Check NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY starts with pk_test_ (dev) or pk_live_ (prod)
    └─ Mismatch between publishable and secret key environments
```

