## DEPLOYMENT DEBUGGING DECISION TREE

```
Works in dev (localhost) but broken on Netlify
│
├─ Check Netlify deploy logs FIRST
│   └─ Netlify Dashboard → your site → Deploys → click failed deploy → read Build log
│
├─ TypeScript build errors?
│   └─ npx tsc --noEmit (run locally — Next.js fails build on any TS error)
│   └─ Emergency unblock: next.config.ts → typescript: { ignoreBuildErrors: true }
│
├─ Missing environment variables?
│   └─ .env.local is NOT auto-synced to Netlify — must add manually
│   └─ Netlify Dashboard → Site → Site Configuration → Environment Variables
│   └─ After adding: Deploys → Trigger deploy → "Clear cache and deploy"
│
├─ Auth/Supabase broken only in production?
│   └─ Add production URL to Supabase Auth → URL Configuration → Site URL + Redirect URLs
│
├─ API routes returning 404?
│   └─ Confirm files are in app/api/[name]/route.ts (App Router pattern)
│   └─ NOT in pages/api/ (Pages Router — different, not used by Rocket)
│   └─ Export name must be: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE (capitalized)
│
├─ "Module not found" build error?
│   └─ Package in .env.local devDependencies but not dependencies
│   └─ Fix: npm install --save [package-name]
│
└─ React SPA routing 404 on page refresh? (React/Vite projects only)
    └─ Create public/_redirects with content: /*  /index.html  200
```

