## ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE CHECKLIST

The silent killer. Check these before anything else in a broken deployed app.

```bash
# Local (.env.local) — required
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL          # https://[id].supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY     # eyJ... (public, safe in browser)
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY         # eyJ... (server only, never NEXT_PUBLIC_)
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY                 # sk_test_... (dev) or sk_live_... (prod)
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY # pk_test_... (dev) or pk_live_... (prod)
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET             # whsec_... (unique per endpoint AND environment)
STRIPE_PRICE_ID                   # price_... (DIFFERENT in test vs live mode)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL              # http://localhost:3000 (dev) or https://[app].netlify.app
RESEND_API_KEY                    # re_... (if using email)
```

**Common env var mistakes:**
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix missing → variable undefined in browser, no error thrown
- `.env.local` not created (only `.env.example` exists) → run `cp .env.example .env.local`
- Wrong quotes in `.env.local` → `KEY="value"` not `KEY=value` (don't use quotes for simple values)
- Netlify vars not updated after going live → Stripe test keys in production

