## EMAIL DEBUGGING DECISION TREE

```
Emails not sending / going to spam
│
├─ Are emails sending at all in production?
│   └─ Check: Resend/SendGrid dashboard → Logs → see if sends are attempted
│   └─ If no sends logged → API key not set in Netlify env vars
│      Fix: Netlify Dashboard → Environment Variables → add RESEND_API_KEY
│
├─ Emails sending but going to spam?
│   └─ From address not using verified domain
│   └─ ❌ from: 'hello@gmail.com' — will always go to spam
│   └─ ✅ from: 'hello@yourdomain.com' — must be verified in Resend dashboard
│   Fix: Resend Dashboard → Domains → Add domain → add DNS records
│
├─ Getting "domain not verified" error?
│   └─ DNS records not propagated yet (can take up to 48 hours)
│   └─ Check: Resend Dashboard → Domains → verify DNS status
│
├─ Email confirmation link broken after deploy?
│   └─ Production URL not added to Supabase Auth → URL Configuration
│   └─ Fix: Add https://your-app.netlify.app to Supabase redirect URLs
│
└─ Works in dev but not production?
    └─ RESEND_API_KEY set in .env.local but NOT in Netlify environment variables
    └─ Fix: Netlify Dashboard → Site Configuration → Environment Variables → add key
    └─ After adding: trigger fresh deploy with "Clear cache and deploy"
```

### Quick Email Diagnostic
```bash
# Check if email API key is present
grep "RESEND_API_KEY\|SENDGRID_API_KEY" .env.local

# Check from address in email sending code
grep -rn "from:" ./app ./lib 2>/dev/null | grep -v ".env"
# Must use verified domain — not gmail, not outlook
```

## RED FLAGS — PATTERNS THAT WILL DEFINITELY CAUSE BUGS

Scan any Rocket project for these on first open:

```bash
# 1. getSession() in server code (broken auth)
grep -rn "getSession()" ./app ./lib ./middleware.ts

# 2. middleware.ts in wrong place
ls ./app/middleware.ts 2>/dev/null && echo "⚠️ WRONG LOCATION"

# 3. Deprecated Supabase package
grep -rn "auth-helpers-nextjs" ./package.json

# 4. request.json() in Stripe webhook
grep -rn "request.json()" ./app/api/webhooks/stripe/

# 5. Missing /auth/callback route (OAuth will fail)
ls ./app/auth/callback/route.ts 2>/dev/null || echo "⚠️ MISSING AUTH CALLBACK"

# 6. Missing middleware (sessions won't refresh)
ls ./middleware.ts 2>/dev/null || ls ./src/middleware.ts 2>/dev/null || echo "⚠️ NO MIDDLEWARE"

# 7. NEXT_PUBLIC_ on service role key (security risk)
grep -rn "NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE" ./.env.local ./app ./lib
```

